HEADWORD: flypaper
<hw>fly"pa`per</hw> <pr>(fl⟦imac⟧"p⟦amac⟧`p⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A strip of paper that is coated with a sticky substance and
suspended from an overhead object to trap and kill flies; also, a
similar paper poisoned so as to kill flies on contact.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

